11912	[A finite product of right-\(f_*\)-acyclic objects is right-\(f_*\)-acyclic]
11913	  \label{lem:rightAcyclic_finite_prod}
11914	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.rightAcyclic_finite_prod}
11915	  \textit{Project-local.}
11916	  Let \(G : \mathcal{A} \to \mathcal{B}\) be an additive functor between abelian
11917	  categories that admits a right-derived functor, and let \((X_s)_{s \in \Sigma}\)
11918	  be a \emph{finite} family of objects of \(\mathcal{A}\), each right
11919	  \(G\)-acyclic --- \(G.\mathrm{rightDerived}\,k\,(X_s) = 0\) for all \(k \geq 1\)
11920	  and all \(s\). Then the product \(\prod_{s \in \Sigma} X_s\) is right
11921	  \(G\)-acyclic: \(G.\mathrm{rightDerived}\,k\,\bigl(\prod_s X_s\bigr) = 0\) for all
11922	  \(k \geq 1\).

